sentences.english: The sophisticated system destroys enemy warheads through direct "hit-to-kill" technology. "It's like hitting a bullet with a bullet," Watkins says.
sentences.chinese: 系統利用命中即摧毀技術，摧毀敵方的彈頭。

sentences.english: Under government policy, British nuclear submarines carry a maximum of 48 warheads.
sentences.chinese: 據政府政策規定，英國核潛艇最多可裝載48顆彈頭。

sentences.english: The effects of perforators nose shapes on the perforation are discussed with the calculated results.
sentences.chinese: 基於計算結果，分析了彈頭部形狀對貫穿過程的影響。

sentences.english: This kind of machine is suitable for thermoforming fabric cups by bullet head moulds.
sentences.chinese: 該機適用於各種布料，子彈頭模具的熱壓定型。

sentences.english: Presumably, the only thing that will mollify Kyl and others would be new warheads.
sentences.chinese: 大概，唯一能讓卡爾和其他人住嘴的是新彈頭。

sentences.english: Each side will cut its arsenal to below 1,700.
sentences.chinese: 雙方均將其核彈頭數量減少到1，700枚以下。

sentences.english: He grabbed the pack with the FENRIS warheads, and swung it over his shoulder.
sentences.chinese: 他抓起裝着芬里斯核彈頭的揹包，甩上了他的肩膀。

sentences.english: India has successfully launched a long-range intercontinental ballistic missile able to carry a nuclear warhead, officials say.
sentences.chinese: 印度成功發射一枚可以攜帶核彈頭的洲際彈道導彈。

sentences.english: The plane also carried nuclear warheads.
sentences.chinese: 這架飛機也同時攜帶核子彈頭。

sentences.english: It would probably take years more to develop a warhead and test it.
sentences.chinese: 伊朗可能還需要很多年來研製彈頭並且進行試驗。

sentences.english: The Iron Nokana is the fifth boss from Metal Slug: Super Vehicle-001.
sentences.chinese: 黑鐵是合金彈頭的第五個頭目。

sentences.english: Objective To evaluate the usefulness of multiple RF needle electrodes in the treatment of hepatic cancer.
sentences.chinese: 目的評價多彈頭集束射頻治療肝癌的實用價值。

sentences.english: It incorporates a steel case and penetrating blast-fragmentation warhead.
sentences.chinese: 它集成了一個不鏽鋼錶殼和穿透殺爆彈頭。

sentences.english: But the United States will not conduct new nuclear testing, and will not develop new nuclear warheads.
sentences.chinese: 但美國將不進行新的核試驗，也不發展新的核彈頭。

sentences.english: Scientists will soon be able to observe the first instants after a nuclear warhead detonates.
sentences.chinese: 科學家不久將能觀察到核彈頭爆炸的第一瞬間。
